stylometry: Our final project was an advertising problem for Cutco Cutlery.  There are various types of advertising methods and certain age groups that we are trying to reach.  We looked at the costs associated with each method, the call rates (per age group) for each method, and the weight of these together.  We ran solver to find the best advertising mix by maintaining a $5000 monthly budget and a minimum amount of applicants received as well.  We learned the best way to set up ads in the area while meeting these restraints.  By doing this, we also learned that many of the advertising methods are not worth the money spent on them.
